{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Add execution-phase plan reviews\n\n## Goal\nAllow plan changes made during implementation to be reviewed without re-litigating low-priority implementation findings, while retaining the stricter planning review when one already exists.\n\n## Implementation\n- Add an internal reducer-maintained plan_review_phase enum to compiled state, distinct from prompt execution_mode: every committed STATUS event targeting in_progress sets execution; every committed event targeting open sets planning; other targets preserve it. Force transitions follow the same target-status rule. Carry it through SNAPSHOT compaction. Review reads it O(1), never scans raw history.\n- When a pre-feature snapshot lacks plan_review_phase, bootstrap planning for compiled status open or idea and execution otherwise. Bump the reducer-cache version so first post-upgrade reduction applies this idempotently; subsequent snapshots persist it.\n- Encode review-phase: planning|execution; execution also encodes priority-floor: 0.80. Absence means legacy planning. A syntactically valid floor is numeric in [0.0, 1.0]; reject unknown phases plus missing, nonnumeric, or range-invalid execution floors.\n- Planning mode accepts only planning. Execution mode accepts planning or execution whose numeric priority-floor is at least 0.80. The fixed 0.80 protocol policy is not configurable. Future policy changes compare the numeric field: raising the requirement invalidates older lower-floor execution reviews; lowering it accepts older higher-floor reviews without a format migration.\n- For an execution review, use effective blocking threshold max(normal criterion threshold, 0.8). Advisory-only criteria remain advisory; deterministic structural failures remain blocking; sub-threshold findings stay visible.\n- Snapshot lifecycle phase and material before review, then recheck both immediately before signing so concurrent transitions or edits cannot certify the wrong mode.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Entry into in_progress sets the compiled plan_review_phase projection.\n- [ ] Entry into open clears the compiled plan_review_phase projection.\n- [ ] Other status transitions preserve the projection.\n- [ ] Compaction snapshots preserve the projection.\n- [ ] Planning reviews sign review-phase: planning.\n- [ ] Execution reviews sign review-phase: execution plus priority-floor: 0.80.\n- [ ] Phase-less legacy attestations behave as planning.\n- [ ] Planning mode rejects execution-phase attestations.\n- [ ] Execution mode accepts planning attestations.\n- [ ] Execution mode accepts execution attestations with a numeric floor at least 0.80.\n- [ ] Malformed phase or floor metadata fails compatibility.\n- [ ] Execution review decisions apply the 0.80 blocking floor.\n- [ ] Sub-floor findings remain visible.\n- [ ] Advisory-only criteria remain advisory.\n- [ ] Deterministic structural failures remain blocking.\n\n## Verification\n- Run focused lifecycle, manifest, threshold, and sign-time concurrency tests.\n- Run make check and the non-integration test suite.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784521000905430001,"uuid":"a0ee244e-a026-48ee-ad33-e66b2c2aa923"}